        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 9:29PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 928 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Divide, or 16 miles west of Colorado Springs, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pikes Peak, Cascade, and Chipita Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
central and east central Colorado.</instruction>
